{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Amend the law on statutory overcrowding and children sharing bedrooms",
        "additional_details": "We believe it is not appropriate for a female and male to be expected to share a room up till the age of 10.\r\n \r\nChildren as young as 8 can enter puberty. We believe the current definition of overcrowding and children sharing bedrooms is not suitable.\r\n",
        "background": "We want the Government to amend the statutory definition of overcrowding so that children aged 8 and over aren't expected to share a room. Currently this only applies to children aged 10 and over. We are particularly concerned about the impact this has in the social housing sector.",
